    "His wrath consumed them like stubble.",
    "The blast of His nostrils piled up waters like a heap.",
    "The enemy boasted of dividing spoil, but Yahweh blew and covered them.",
    "They sank like lead in mighty waters.",
    "No god is like Yahweh—glorious in holiness, doing wonders.",
    "Yahweh stretched out His hand and the earth swallowed them.",
    "In His loving kindness, He led His redeemed people.",
    "Nations trembled at what they heard.",
    "Edom and Moab were dismayed; Canaan melted away.",
    "Terror fell on them until Israel passed over.",
    "Yahweh would bring them to His holy habitation.",
    "Yahweh would reign forever.",
    "Pharaoh’s horses and chariots went into the sea, but Israel walked on dry land.",
    "Miriam the prophetess took a tambourine and led women in dance.",
    "She sang, 'Sing to Yahweh, for He has triumphed gloriously.'",
    "Moses led Israel from the Red Sea into the wilderness of Shur.",
    "After three days, they found no water.",
    "At Marah, the water was bitter, so they called it Marah.",
    "The people murmured against Moses, asking what to drink.",
    "Moses cried to Yahweh, who showed him a tree to sweeten the water.",
    "There God gave statutes and tested them.",
    "He promised no diseases if they obeyed His commandments.",
    "They came to Elim, with twelve springs and seventy palm trees, and camped.",
    "They journeyed to the wilderness of Sin and murmured against Moses and Aaron.",
    "They wished to have died in Egypt with full bellies rather than starve.",
    "God promised to rain bread from heaven and test their obedience.",
    "On the sixth day, they would gather double.",
    "Moses said in the evening they would know Yahweh brought them out.",
    "In the morning, they would see His glory because He heard their murmurings.",
    "Moses said God would give them meat in the evening and bread in the morning.",
    "God heard their murmurings, not against Moses but against Him.",
    "Moses told Aaron to bring the people before Yahweh.",
    "As Aaron spoke, the glory of Yahweh appeared in the cloud.",
    "God said He heard their murmurings and would give meat and bread.",
    "That evening, quail covered the camp; in the morning, dew lay around.",
    "When it evaporated, manna like frost was on the ground.",
    "They asked, 'What is it?' not knowing. Moses said it was bread from God.",
    "Each was to gather an omer per person.",
    "They gathered more or less, but when measured, all had enough.",
    "Moses told them not to leave any until morning.",
    "Some did, and it bred worms and stank. Moses was angry.",
    "They gathered it daily; when the sun grew hot, it melted.",
    "On the sixth day, they gathered double. Rulers told Moses.",
    "He said it was because the next day was the Sabbath.",
    "They were to bake and boil what they needed and keep the rest.",
    "They kept it until morning and it did not spoil.",
    "Moses said to eat it that day, as no manna would be found in the field.",
    "They were to gather six days, but none on the seventh.",
    "Some went out on the seventh day and found none.",
    "God asked Moses how long they would refuse to keep His commandments.",
    "He gave double on the sixth day so they could rest on the Sabbath.",
    "No one should leave their place on the seventh day.",
    "The people rested on the seventh day.",
    "The house of Israel called it manna; it was like coriander seed and tasted like honey wafers.",
    "Moses said an omer should be kept as a memorial of God’s provision.",
    "He told Aaron to put it in a jar before Yahweh.",
    "Aaron did so, as commanded.",
    "Israel ate manna forty years until they reached inhabited land.",
    "An omer was one-tenth of an ephah.",
    "The whole congregation traveled to Rephidim but found no water.",
    "The people quarreled with Moses, demanding water.",
    "Moses asked why they tested God.",
    "They were thirsty and accused Moses of bringing them to die.",
    "Moses cried to God, fearing they would stone him.",
    "God told Moses to take elders and his rod and go to Horeb.",
    "God would stand on the rock; Moses was to strike it for water.",
    "Moses did so before the elders.",
    "He named the place Massah and Meribah because they tested God.",
    "They asked if God was among them or not.",
    "Then Amalek came and fought Israel at Rephidim.",
    "Moses told Joshua to choose men and fight Amalek.",
    "Moses would stand on the hill with God’s rod.",
    "Joshua fought, and Moses, Aaron, and Hur went to the hilltop.",
    "When Moses held up his hand, Israel prevailed; when down, Amalek prevailed.",
    "Moses’ hands grew heavy, so Aaron and Hur held them up until sunset.",
    "Joshua defeated Amalek with the sword.",
    "God told Moses to write a memorial and tell Joshua He would blot out Amalek.",
    "Moses built an altar and called it Yahweh our Banner.",
    "He said Yahweh would have war with Amalek generation to generation.",
    "Jethro, Moses’ father-in-law, heard what God did and came to visit.",
    "He brought Zipporah, Moses’ wife, and their two sons.",
    "One son was Gershom, meaning 'a foreigner in a foreign land.'",
    "The other was Eliezer, meaning 'God is my help.'",
    "Jethro came to Moses at the mountain of God with his family.",
    "He said he had come to Moses with his wife and sons.",
    "Moses greeted him, bowed, kissed him, and they asked of peace.",
    "Moses told Jethro all God had done to Egypt and how He delivered them.",
    "Jethro rejoiced at God’s goodness to Israel.",
    "He blessed Yahweh for delivering Israel from Egypt and Pharaoh.",
    "He said now he knew Yahweh was greater than all gods.",
    "Jethro offered burnt offerings and sacrifices, and Aaron and elders ate with him.",
    "The next day, Moses judged the people from morning to evening.",
    "Jethro saw this and asked why Moses alone bore the burden.",
    "Moses said the people came to inquire of God and he judged disputes.",
    "Jethro said this was not good; Moses would wear out.",
    "He advised Moses to represent the people before God and teach laws.",
    "He should appoint able, God-fearing men as leaders over thousands, hundreds, fifties, tens.",
    "They would judge small matters; only hard cases would come to Moses.",
    "This would ease the load, and Moses could endure.",
    "Moses listened and did as advised.",
    "He chose able men and made them leaders.",
    "They judged daily; hard cases went to Moses.",
    "Moses let Jethro go home.",
    "In the third month, Israel came to Sinai and camped before the mountain.",
    "Moses went up, and God called to him from the mountain.",
    "God told Moses to tell Jacob’s house and Israel what He had done.",
    "He had borne them on eagles’ wings and brought them to Himself.",
    "If they obeyed and kept His covenant, they would be His treasured possession.",
    "All the earth was His, but they would be a kingdom of priests and holy nation.",
    "Moses told the elders, and they agreed to do all Yahweh said.",
    "God told Moses He would come in a cloud so the people would believe forever.",
    "Moses was to sanctify the people and have them wash garments.",
    "They were to be ready by the third day when God would come down.",
    "They were not to touch the mountain or they would die.",
    "No hand was to touch anyone who did; they were to be stoned or shot.",
    "When the trumpet sounded long, they could approach.",
    "Moses went down, sanctified the people, and they washed clothes.",
    "He told them to be ready and avoid sexual relations.",
    "On the third day, there were thunder, lightning, a thick cloud, and loud trumpet.",
    "The people trembled.",
    "Moses led them to the mountain’s base.",
    "Mount Sinai smoked because God descended in fire; it quaked greatly.",
    "As the trumpet grew louder, Moses spoke and God answered.",
    "God came down and called Moses to the top.",
    "He told Moses to warn the people not to break through, or many would die.",
    "Priests who approached must sanctify themselves.",
    "Moses said the people could not come up because God had warned them.",
    "God told Moses to bring Aaron up but not let priests or people break through.",
    "Moses went down and told them.",
    "God spoke all these words: 'I am Yahweh your God who brought you out of Egypt.'",
    "You shall have no other gods before Me.",
    "You shall not make idols or worship them.",
    "I, Yahweh, am a jealous God, punishing children for parents’ sins.",
    "I show mercy to thousands who love Me and keep My commandments.",
    "You shall not misuse the name of Yahweh.",
    "Remember the Sabbath day and keep it holy.",
    "Work six days, but the seventh is a Sabbath to Yahweh.",
    "In six days Yahweh made heaven, earth, sea, and all; He rested and blessed the day.",
    "Honor your father and mother, that your days may be long.",
    "You shall not murder.",
    "You shall not commit adultery.",
    "You shall not steal.",
    "You shall not give false testimony.",
    "You shall not covet your neighbor’s house, wife, servants, animals, or possessions.",
    "The people saw thunder, lightning, trumpet, and smoking mountain and trembled.",
    "They told Moses to speak to them, but not God, lest they die.",
    "Moses said not to fear, for God came to test them and prevent sin.",
    "The people stayed back; Moses entered the thick darkness where God was.",
    "God told Moses to tell Israel they had seen Him speak from heaven.",
    "They were not to make silver or gold gods alongside Him.",
    "They were to make an earth altar and sacrifice burnt and peace offerings.",
    "Wherever He recorded His name, He would come and bless.",
    "If they made a stone altar, it must not be cut or have steps.",
    "These are the ordinances to set before them.",
    "A Hebrew servant serves six years and goes free in the seventh.",
    "If he came alone, he leaves alone; if married, his wife goes too.",
    "If his master gave him a wife and children, they stay; he leaves alone.",
    "If he declares he loves his master, wife, and children and will not leave,",
    "His master brings him to God and pierces his ear; he serves forever.",
    "If a man sells his daughter as a servant, she does not go free like males.",
    "If she displeases her master, he must let her be redeemed, not sell her.",
    "If he marries her to his son, he must treat her as a daughter.",
    "If he takes another wife, he must not diminish her food, clothing, or rights.",
    "If he fails, she goes free without payment.",
    "Whoever strikes a man so he dies shall be put to death.",
    "But if it was unintentional and God allowed it, a place of refuge is provided.",
    "If one schemes to kill, he shall be taken from the altar and die.",
    "Anyone who attacks father or mother shall be put to death.",
    "Whoever kidnaps and sells someone, or is caught with him, shall die.",
    "Whoever curses father or mother shall be put to death.",
    "If men fight and one is struck but does not die, the striker pays healing costs.",
    "If a man strikes his servant and they die, he is punished.",
    "But if they live a day or two, he is not punished, as they are his property.",
    "If men fight and hurt a pregnant woman so she miscarries but no harm follows,",
    "He is fined as the husband demands and judges allow.",
    "But if harm follows, life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, and so on.",
    "If a man destroys his servant’s eye, he must let the servant go free.",
    "If he knocks out a tooth, the servant goes free.",
    "If a bull gores someone to death, the bull is stoned and not eaten.",
    "The owner is not liable unless the bull was known to gore and not kept in.",
    "Then both bull and owner are put to death, unless a ransom is set.",
    "If the bull gores a son or daughter, the same applies.",
    "If it gores a servant, the owner pays thirty shekels and the bull is stoned.",
    "If a man opens or digs a pit and does not cover it, and an animal falls in,",
    "He must pay the owner; the dead animal is his.",
    "If one man’s bull injures another’s so it dies, they sell the live bull and divide proceeds.",
    "They also divide the dead animal.",
    "But if the bull was known to gore and owner did not keep it in, he pays bull for bull.",
    "The dead animal is his own.",
    "If a man steals an ox or sheep and kills or sells it, he pays five oxen or four sheep.",
    "If a thief is caught breaking in and is struck dead, no blood guilt.",
    "But if it is daylight, blood guilt applies; he must make restitution.",
    "If he has nothing, he is sold for his theft.",
    "If stolen property is found alive in his hand, he pays double.",
    "If a man lets his animal graze in another’s field, he must repay from the best.",
    "If fire spreads and burns grain, he must make restitution.",
    "If a man delivers goods to a neighbor for safekeeping and they are stolen,",
    "If thief is found, he pays double; if not, master of house swears before God.",
    "For any dispute, both parties come before God; the guilty pays double.",
    "If a man delivers an animal to a neighbor and it dies or is lost unseen,",
    "An oath before God clears the keeper; owner accepts it.",
    "But if stolen, he must repay owner.",
    "If torn, he brings proof and is not liable.",
    "If a man borrows and animal is injured or dies without owner present, he must repay.",
    "If owner is present, no repayment; if leased, no issue.",
    "If a man seduces a virgin not pledged, he must pay her dowry to marry her.",
    "If her father refuses, he pays the dowry of virgins.",
    "You shall not let a sorceress live.",
    "Whoever has sex with an animal shall be put to death.",
    "Whoever sacrifices to any god except Yahweh shall be destroyed.",
    "Do not wrong or oppress an alien, for you were aliens in Egypt.",
    "Do not take advantage of widows or fatherless children.",
    "If you do and they cry to Me, I will hear and kill you with the sword.",
    "Your wives will be widows, your children fatherless.",
    "If you lend to the poor, do not act as a creditor or charge interest.",
    "If you take a neighbor’s garment as collateral, return it before sunset.",
    "It is his only covering; I will hear if he cries to Me.",
    "Do not curse God or a ruler of your people.",
    "Do not delay offering from your harvest or presses.",
    "Give the firstborn of your sons to Me.",
    "Do the same for cattle and sheep; give it on the eighth day.",
    "You shall be holy; do not eat flesh torn by animals in the field—throw it to dogs.",
    "Do not spread false reports or join hands with the wicked as a false witness.",
    "Do not follow a crowd to do evil or testify to pervert justice.",
    "Do not favor a poor man in his cause.",
    "If you meet your enemy’s ox or donkey going astray, return it.",
    "If you see your enemy’s donkey fallen, help him lift it.",
    "Do not deny justice to the poor in their lawsuits.",
    "Keep far from a false charge; do not kill the innocent.",
    "Do not take bribes, for they blind the clear and pervert the righteous.",
    "Do not oppress an alien; you know the heart of an alien, for you were aliens.",
    "Sow your land six years and gather its increase.",
    "Let it rest the seventh year so the poor may eat and animals consume the rest.",
    "Do the same with vineyard and olive grove.",
    "Work six days, rest on the seventh, so your animals and servants may refresh.",
    "Be careful to do all I have said; do not invoke other gods.",
    "Observe three feasts to Me yearly.",
    "Keep the feast of unleavened bread; eat unleavened bread seven days.",
    "No one appears before Me empty.",
    "Keep the feast of harvest with first fruits of your labor.",
    "Keep the feast of ingathering at year’s end.",
    "Three times a year, all males appear before the Lord Yahweh.",
    "Do not offer My sacrifice with leavened bread.",
    "Do not let fat of My feast remain overnight.",
    "Bring first of first fruits to Yahweh’s house.",
    "Do not boil a young goat in its mother’s milk.",
    "Behold, I send an angel before you to guide you to the place I prepared.",
    "Pay attention to him and obey; he will not pardon rebellion, for My name is in him.",
    "If you obey him, I will be an enemy to your enemies.",
    "My angel will bring you to the Amorite, Hittite, and others; I will cut them off.",
    "Do not bow to their gods or follow their practices; destroy their pillars.",
    "Serve Yahweh; He will bless your food and water and remove sickness.",
    "No one will miscarry or be barren; I will fulfill your days.",
    "I will send My terror ahead and make enemies turn their backs.",
    "I will send hornets to drive out Hivite, Canaanite, and Hittite.",
    "I will not drive them out in one year, lest land become desolate.",
    "Little by little I will drive them out as you increase.",
    "I will set your border from Red Sea to Philistine Sea, from wilderness to River.",
    "I will deliver inhabitants into your hand; you will drive them out.",
    "Make no covenant with them or their gods.",
    "They must not dwell in your land, lest they make you sin.",
    "God told Moses to come up with Aaron, Nadab, Abihu, and seventy elders.",
    "They would worship from a distance; only Moses would come near.",
    "Moses told the people all God’s words and ordinances.",
    "All the people answered together, 'All that Yahweh has spoken, we will do.'",
    "Moses wrote God’s words, built an altar and twelve pillars for the tribes.",
    "Young men offered burnt and peace offerings.",
    "Moses took half the blood and put it in basins, half he sprinkled on the altar.",
    "He read the book of the covenant; they said, 'We will do and obey.'",
    "Moses sprinkled the blood on the people, saying, 'This is the blood of the covenant.'",
    "Moses, Aaron, Nadab, Abihu, and seventy elders went up.",
    "They saw the God of Israel; under His feet was sapphire like clear skies.",
    "He did not lay His hand on them; they saw God and ate and drank.",
    "God told Moses to come up; He would give stone tablets with law and commandments.",
    "Moses rose with Joshua and went up the mountain.",
    "He told elders to wait; Aaron and Hur were with them for disputes.",
    "Moses went up; the cloud covered the mountain.",
    "Yahweh’s glory settled on Sinai; the cloud covered it six days.",
    "On the seventh, God called Moses from the cloud.",
    "His glory looked like devouring fire to Israel.",
    "Moses entered the cloud and was on the mountain forty days and nights.",
    "God told Moses to take an offering from willing hearts for a sanctuary.",
    "Materials included gold, silver, brass, blue, purple, scarlet, linen, goat hair,",
    "Rams’ skins, sea cow hides, acacia wood, oil, spices, incense, onyx, and setting stones.",
    "They were to make a sanctuary so God could dwell among them.",
    "They were to make it according to the pattern shown on the mountain.",
    "They would make an ark of acacia wood, overlaid with gold inside and out.",
    "It would have a gold molding and four gold rings for poles.",
    "Poles would stay in the rings; the testimony would be placed inside.",
    "A mercy seat of pure gold with two cherubim of hammered gold would cover it.",
    "Cherubim wings would cover the seat, facing each other and the seat.",
    "The mercy seat would go on the ark; the testimony inside.",
    "God would meet with Moses from above the mercy seat between the cherubim.",
    "A table of acacia wood overlaid with gold would hold the bread of presence.",
    "It would have gold rings and poles, dishes, spoons, bowls, and pitchers of gold.",
    "A lampstand of pure gold, made of one piece, would give light.",
    "It would have seven lamps, snuffers, and snuff dishes of gold.",
    "It would be made from one talent of gold.",
    "They were to make the tabernacle with ten curtains of fine linen and colors.",
    "Each curtain was twenty-eight cubits long and four wide; five coupled together.",
    "Loops of blue and fifty gold clasps joined them into one unit.",
    "Eleven curtains of goat hair would cover the tabernacle.",
    "Each was thirty cubits long; five and six were coupled.",
    "Fifty loops and fifty brass clasps joined them.",
    "A covering of red rams’ skins and sea cow hides would go above.",
    "Boards of acacia wood, ten cubits long and one and a half wide, would stand up.",
    "Twenty boards for south and north sides, each with two silver sockets.",
    "Six boards for the west end, two corner boards, eight in total with sixteen sockets.",
    "Five bars of acacia wood overlaid with gold would hold each side.",
    "The middle bar would pass through the midst.",
    "They would hang a veil of colors with cherubim on four gold pillars with silver sockets.",
    "The veil would separate the holy place from the most holy, where the ark would be.",
    "The table would be outside the veil on the north; lampstand on the south.",
    "A screen of colors for the tent door would have five acacia pillars with brass sockets.",
    "The altar of acacia wood, five cubits square and three high, would have horns.",
    "It would be overlaid with brass, with utensils of brass.",
    "A bronze grating would go halfway up, with rings and poles for carrying.",
    "It would be hollow.",
    "The court would have linen hangings one hundred cubits long on south and north.",
    "Fifty cubits on west, fifty on east with fifteen-cubit hangings on each side.",
    "The gate screen would be twenty cubits of colors with four pillars.",
    "All pillars would have silver fillets and brass sockets.",
    "The court would be one hundred by fifty cubits, five high.",
    "All instruments and pins would be brass.",
    "They were to bring pure olive oil for the lamp to burn continually.",
    "Aaron and sons would keep it burning from evening to morning as a statute.",
    "Bring Aaron and his sons to minister as priests.",
    "Make holy garments for Aaron for glory and beauty.",
    "Wise-hearted men would make them.",
    "Garments: breastplate, ephod, robe, tunic, turban, sash.",
    "Materials: gold, blue, purple, scarlet, fine linen.",
    "The ephod would be of gold and colors, with two shoulder straps.",
    "A skillfully woven band would match.",
    "Two onyx stones with names of Israel’s sons would be set in gold on shoulders.",
    "They would be stones of memorial.",
    "Chains of pure gold like cords would connect to settings.",
    "The breastplate of judgment would be square, double, made like the ephod.",
    "Four rows of stones: ruby, topaz, beryl; turquoise, sapphire, emerald;",
    "Jacinth, agate, amethyst; chrysolite, onyx, jasper—each in gold settings.",
    "Twelve stones for twelve tribes, like signets.",
    "Chains of gold like cords would attach to rings on breastplate ends.",
    "Rings on breastplate and ephod would connect with blue lace.",
    "Aaron would bear the tribes’ names on his heart as a memorial.",
    "Urim and Thummim would be in the breastplate for judgment.",
    "The robe of the ephod would be all blue with a woven hole.",
    "Pomegranates and golden bells would be on its hem.",
    "The sound would be heard when Aaron ministered, so he would not die.",
    "A plate of pure gold engraved 'HOLY TO YAHWEH' would be on the sash.",
    "It would be on Aaron’s forehead to bear iniquity of holy things.",
    "A tunic of fine linen, turban, and embroidered sash would be made.",
    "Coats, sashes, and headbands for Aaron’s sons would be for glory.",
    "They would be anointed and consecrated to serve as priests.",
    "Linen breeches would cover nakedness from waist to thighs.",
    "They would wear them when entering the tent or approaching the altar.",
    "This would be a perpetual statute.",
    "To consecrate priests: take a bull and two rams without blemish.",
    "Unleavened bread, cakes, and wafers of fine flour mixed with oil.",
    "Bring them in a basket with the animals.",
    "Bring Aaron and sons to the tent door and wash them.",
    "Put on Aaron the coat, robe, ephod, breastplate, and sash.",
    "Set the turban on his head and the holy crown on it.",
    "Pour anointing oil on his head.",
    "Put coats on his sons and clothe them with belts and headbands.",
    "They would have the priesthood by perpetual statute.",
    "Bring the bull; Aaron and sons lay hands on its head.",
    "Kill it before Yahweh; put blood on altar horns and pour rest at base.",
    "Burn fat, liver cover, kidneys, and fat on altar.",
    "Burn flesh, skin, and dung outside camp as sin offering.",
    "Take one ram; lay hands on its head, kill it, sprinkle blood on altar.",
    "Cut it in pieces, wash innards and legs, place on altar, burn whole as burnt offering.",
    "Take second ram; lay hands on its head, kill it.",
    "Put blood on right ear, right hand, right foot of Aaron and sons.",
    "Sprinkle rest on altar.",
    "Take blood and anointing oil, sprinkle on Aaron, his garments, sons, and their garments.",
    "Take fat, tail, innards, liver cover, kidneys, right thigh, bread, cake, wafer.",
    "Put all in Aaron’s hands and wave as wave offering.",
    "Take from their hands and burn on altar as offering.",
    "Take the breast of the ram of consecration and wave it as your portion.",
    "Sanctify the breast and thigh as portions for Aaron and sons forever.",
    "Aaron’s holy garments would pass to his sons to be anointed in.",
    "Each priest would wear them seven days when entering the tent.",
    "Boil the ram of consecration in a holy place.",
    "Aaron and sons would eat its flesh and the bread at the tent door.",
    "Strangers could not eat, for they are holy.",
    "Leftovers in morning must be burned; not eaten.",
    "Do this for seven days to consecrate them.",
    "Offer the bull of sin offering daily for seven days to cleanse the altar.",
    "Anoint it to sanctify it; it will be most holy.",
    "Offer two lambs daily: one in morning, one at evening.",
    "With morning lamb: fine flour, oil, wine for drink offering.",
    "Same for evening lamb.",
    "It is a continual burnt offering before Yahweh.",
    "There He will meet Israel and speak.",
    "His glory will sanctify the place.",
    "He will sanctify the tent, altar, Aaron, and sons to serve.",
    "He will dwell among Israel and be their God.",
    "They will know He is Yahweh who brought them out to dwell among them.",
    "Make an altar of acacia wood for incense, one cubit square, two high.",
    "Horns of one piece; overlay with pure gold and make gold molding.",
    "Make two golden rings on sides for poles of acacia overlaid with gold.",
    "Put it before the veil, before the mercy seat, where He will meet with Moses.",
    "Aaron will burn sweet incense every morning and evening as a perpetual incense.",
    "No strange incense, burnt offering, meal offering, or drink offering on it.",
    "Aaron will make atonement on its horns once a year with sin offering blood.",
    "It is most holy to Yahweh.",
    "When taking a census, each man gives half a shekel as ransom.",
    "No plague will come if they give it.",
    "Rich and poor give the same; it is an offering to make atonement.",
    "Take the atonement money for the tent’s service as a memorial.",
    "Make a brass basin with base for washing between tent and altar.",
    "Aaron and sons will wash hands and feet when entering or approaching altar.",
    "They will not die; it is a perpetual statute.",
    "Make holy anointing oil with myrrh, cinnamon, cane, cassia, and olive oil.",
    "It is a sacred perfume; anoint the tent, ark, table, lampstand, altars, basin.",
    "Sanctify them; whatever touches them becomes holy.",
    "Anoint Aaron and sons to sanctify them for priesthood.",
    "This oil is holy; not to be poured on flesh or made in same composition.",
    "Whoever makes like it or puts it on a stranger shall be cut off.",
    "Make incense of gum resin, onycha, galbanum, and pure frankincense in equal parts.",
    "Make it a pure, holy perfume, seasoned with salt.",
    "Beat some small and put before the testimony; it is most holy.",
    "Do not make incense like it; whoever does shall be cut off.",
    "Bezalel son of Uri is called by name, filled with God’s Spirit for wisdom,",
    "Understanding, knowledge, and all craftsmanship, to work in gold, silver, brass,",
    "Cut stones, carve wood, and do all skillful work.",
    "Oholiab son of Ahisamach is appointed with him; God has given wisdom to all able-hearted.",
    "They will make the tent, ark, mercy seat, furniture, garments, oil, and incense.",
    "Speak to Israel: keep My Sabbaths as a sign between Me and you.",
    "It is holy; whoever profanes it or works on it shall be cut off or put to death.",
    "Six days work, seventh day rest; it is a perpetual covenant.",
    "It is a sign forever; in six days Yahweh made all, rested on the seventh.",
    "God gave Moses two stone tablets written by His finger when He finished speaking.",
    "When people saw Moses delayed, they gathered to Aaron and demanded gods.",
    "Aaron told them to bring gold rings; they gave him their jewelry.",
    "He fashioned it into a molten calf and proclaimed a feast to Yahweh.",
    "They offered sacrifices, ate, drank, and rose to play.",
    "God told Moses the people had corrupted themselves with a molten calf.",
    "They had turned from His way; He would consume them and make Moses a great nation.",
    "Moses pleaded for the people, citing God’s promise to Abraham, Isaac, and Israel.",
    "God relented from the evil He said He would do.",
    "Moses came down with the two tablets, written on both sides by God.",
    "Joshua heard shouting and thought it was war; Moses said it was singing.",
    "Moses saw the calf and dancing; his anger burned, and he broke the tablets.",
    "He burned the calf, ground it to powder, scattered it on water, made Israel drink.",
    "Moses asked Aaron what the people did to make him sin.",
    "Aaron said they demanded gods; he threw gold in fire and out came the calf.",
    "Moses saw the people were unrestrained; Aaron had let them loose.",
    "He stood in camp gate and called, 'Whoever is for Yahweh, come to me!'",
    "All Levites gathered, and he told them to kill brother, companion, neighbor.",
    "They did so, and about three thousand men fell.",
    "Moses said they had consecrated themselves to Yahweh, even against sons and brothers.",
    "The next day, Moses said the people sinned greatly; he would seek atonement.",
    "He returned to God, asking forgiveness or to be blotted from His book.",
    "God said whoever sinned against Him would be blotted out.",
    "He told Moses to lead the people; His angel would go before them.",
    "He would punish them later for their sin.",
    "God struck the people for making the calf.",
    "God told Moses to leave with the people to the promised land.",
    "He would send an angel to drive out nations, but would not go with them.",
    "He said they were stiff-necked; if He went, He would consume them.",
    "The people mourned and removed jewelry.",
    "God told Moses they were stiff-necked; He would not go up with them.",
    "He told Moses to remove jewelry so He would know what to do.",
    "Israel stripped off jewelry from Horeb onward.",
    "Moses pitched the tent outside camp, called it the Tent of Meeting.",
    "Whoever sought Yahweh went there.",
    "When Moses went, people stood at tent doors and watched.",
    "When he entered, the cloud descended and spoke with him.",
    "People saw the cloud and worshiped at their tent doors.",
    "Yahweh spoke to Moses face to face, as a man speaks to a friend.",
    "Joshua, a young man, did not leave the tent.",
