    "He would be gracious and merciful to whom He would.",
    "But Moses could not see His face, for no man sees God and lives.",
    "God said to stand on the rock; He would cover Moses in a cleft until He passed.",
    "Then Moses would see His back, but not His face.",
    "God told Moses to chisel two stone tablets like the first.",
    "He would write the words Moses broke.",
    "Be ready by morning and come up Sinai alone.",
    "No one or animal should be seen on the mountain.",
    "Moses chiseled the tablets and went up early as commanded.",
    "Yahweh descended in the cloud, stood with him, and proclaimed His name.",
    "Yahweh passed by and proclaimed, 'Merciful, gracious, slow to anger,",
    "Abundant in loving kindness and truth, keeping kindness for thousands,",
    "Forgiving iniquity, sin, and rebellion, yet not clearing the guilty,",
    "Visiting iniquity of fathers on children to the third and fourth generation.'",
    "Moses bowed and worshiped.",
    "He pleaded, 'If I have found favor, go among us, pardon our sin, take us as inheritance.'",
    "God said He would make a covenant and do marvels unseen in any nation.",
    "He would drive out Amorite, Canaanite, Hittite, Perizzite, Hivite, Jebusite.",
    "Be careful not to make a covenant with them, lest it be a snare.",
    "Break down their altars, dash pillars, cut down Asherim.",
    "Worship no other god; Yahweh is jealous.",
    "Do not make a covenant, lest they lead you to worship their gods.",
    "Do not make cast idols.",
    "Keep the feast of unleavened bread; eat unleavened bread seven days in Abib.",
    "All firstborn are Mine; firstborn males of livestock.",
    "Redeem firstborn donkey with a lamb; if not, break its neck.",
