    "They saw his face shone; he veiled it again until next speaking.",
    "Moses assembled all Israel and gave Yahweh’s commands.",
    "Six days work, seventh day holy Sabbath; whoever works shall be put to death.",
    "No fire kindled in dwellings on Sabbath.",
    "Take an offering from willing hearts: gold, silver, brass,",
    "Blue, purple, scarlet, fine linen, goat hair, rams’ skins, sea cow hides,",
    "Oil, spices, incense, onyx, setting stones.",
    "Let every wise-hearted come and make what Yahweh commanded:",
    "The tabernacle, coverings, clasps, boards, bars, pillars, sockets,",
    "Ark, poles, mercy seat, veil,",
    "Table, poles, vessels, show bread,",
    "Lampstand, vessels, lamps, oil,",
    "Altar of incense, poles, oil, incense, screen,",
    "Altar of burnt offering, grating, vessels, basin, base,",
    "Court hangings, pillars, sockets, gate screen, cords, pins,",
    "Holy garments for Aaron and sons.",
    "All left Moses’ presence.",
    "Everyone whose heart stirred came with offerings for the work.",
    "Men and women brought gold jewelry,",
    "Materials: blue, purple, scarlet, linen, goat hair, skins, wood.",
    "Silver, brass, acacia wood for service were brought.",
    "Wise-hearted women spun yarns of colors and goat hair.",
    "Rulers brought onyx, setting stones, spices, oil, incense.",
    "All who were willing brought freewill offerings.",
    "Moses said Bezalel was called by name, filled with God’s Spirit for wisdom,",
    "To do all workmanship in gold, silver, brass, stone, wood.",
    "He and Oholiab were filled with wisdom to teach others.",
    "All wise-hearted were filled to do engraving, weaving, embroidery.",
    "Bezalel, Oholiab, and all wise-hearted worked on the tabernacle.",
    "Moses called them and all whose hearts were stirred to come.",
    "They received all offerings brought for the work.",
    "They continued bringing offerings every morning.",
    "Wise men told Moses the people brought more than enough.",
    "Moses proclaimed no more offerings for the sanctuary.",
    "The materials were sufficient and too much.",
    "Wise-hearted men made the tabernacle with ten curtains of colors and cherubim.",
    "Each curtain twenty-eight cubits long, four wide; five coupled together.",
    "Fifty loops of blue and fifty gold clasps joined them into one unit.",
    "Eleven goat hair curtains were made, thirty cubits long.",
    "Five and six were coupled; fifty loops and fifty brass clasps joined them.",
    "A covering of red rams’ skins and sea cow hides went above.",
    "Boards of acacia wood, ten cubits long, one and a half wide, stood up.",
    "Each had two tenons; all made alike.",
    "Twenty boards for south and north, each with two silver sockets.",
    "Six for west end, two corner boards, eight total with sixteen sockets.",
    "Five bars of acacia wood overlaid with gold held each side.",
    "Middle bar passed through midst.",
    "Boards overlaid with gold; rings and bars overlaid with gold.",
    "The veil of colors with cherubim was made by a skillful workman.",
    "Four acacia pillars overlaid with gold, hooks of gold, sockets of silver.",
    "A screen for the tent door of colors was made by an embroiderer.",
    "Five pillars with hooks; capitals and fillets overlaid with gold, sockets brass.",
    "Bezalel made the ark of acacia wood, overlaid with gold inside and out.",
    "It had a gold molding, four rings, poles to carry it.",
    "He made the mercy seat of gold with two cherubim of one piece.",
    "Wings covered the seat; faces toward each other and the seat.",
    "The table was of acacia wood, overlaid with gold, with vessels of gold.",
    "The lampstand was of pure gold, one piece, with seven lamps, snuffers, dishes.",
    "It was made from one talent of gold.",
    "The altar of incense was of acacia wood, overlaid with gold, with rings and poles.",
    "He made the anointing oil and incense as commanded.",
    "He made the altar of burnt offering of acacia wood, overlaid with brass.",
    "It had horns, utensils of brass, a bronze grating, rings, and poles.",
    "It was hollow.",
    "He made the basin of brass from mirrors of women serving at the tent door.",
    "He made the court with linen hangings, silver hooks, brass sockets.",
    "The gate screen was of colors with four pillars.",
    "All pins were brass.",
    "The materials used: 29 talents and 730 shekels of gold.",
    "100 talents and 1,775 shekels of silver from 603,550 men.",
    "70 talents and 2,400 shekels of brass.",
    "Bezalel made all as God commanded Moses.",
    "With him was Oholiab, an engraver and embroiderer.",
    "They made garments for Aaron and sons as commanded.",
