    "The breastplate was square, double, with four rows of twelve stones.",
    "Chains, rings, and blue lace connected it to the ephod.",
    "The robe was all blue with pomegranates and golden bells on the hem.",
    "Coats, turban, breeches, sash, and crown were made as commanded.",
    "The plate was engraved 'HOLY TO YAHWEH' and tied with blue lace.",
    "All work of the tabernacle was finished; Israel did as commanded.",
    "They brought all items to Moses.",
    "He saw all was done as Yahweh commanded and blessed them.",
    "God told Moses to set up the tabernacle on the first day of the first month.",
    "Put the ark in it and screen it with the veil.",
    "Bring in the table, set its bread; bring in the lampstand and light lamps.",
    "Set the golden altar for incense before the ark and hang the screen.",
    "Set the altar of burnt offering before the tent door.",
    "Set the basin between tent and altar with water.",
    "Set up the court and hang the gate screen.",
    "Anoint the tabernacle, all its furniture, and sanctify them.",
    "Anoint the altar of burnt offering and sanctify it; it will be most holy.",
    "Anoint the basin and base and sanctify them.",
    "Bring Aaron and sons to the tent door, wash them.",
    "Put holy garments on Aaron, anoint and sanctify him to serve.",
    "Put coats on his sons, anoint them as priests forever.",
    "Moses did all as commanded.",
    "The tabernacle was raised on the first day of the second year.",
    "Moses set up the tabernacle, laid sockets, set boards, bars, pillars.",
    "He spread coverings over it.",
    "He put the testimony in the ark, set poles, put on mercy seat.",
    "He brought the ark into the tabernacle and hung the veil.",
    "He put the table on the north side and set the bread.",
    "He put the lampstand on the south and lit the lamps.",
    "He put the golden altar before the veil and burned incense.",
